The paper proposes a new algorithm for Bayesian optimization that is designed to scale to high dimensions. This is a problem that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), control systems (cs.SY), and data structures (cs.DS). Given that the paper focuses on optimization and learning, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE. However, the paper also discusses control systems and the use of subspaces, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.SY or cs.DS as well.
